# Button

A IDS Button is an element that enables a user to take an action;
initiating a process, committing a change or completing a step in a task.

They are commonly found inside forms, dialogs, panels and screens. Some examples of actions triggered by buttons are, submitting a form, opening a dialog, cancelling an action, or performing a command such as inserting a new record or displaying information hidden on the screen.

## Installation & Import

```bash
yarn add @ids-ts/button
```

```tsx
import { Button } from '@ids-ts/button';
```

## Props API

| Prop | Type | Required | Description |
| --- | --- | --- | --- |
| `automationId` | `string` | No | This prop is used for testing purposes |
| `size` | `Size` | No | - |
| `purpose` | `Purpose` | No | - |
| `priority` | `Priority` | No | - |
| `fullWidth` | `boolean \| 'responsive'` | No | Controls button width. `true` = always full width. `false` = content width (default). `'responsive'` = full width on mobile, content width on desktop. |
| `disabled` | `boolean` | No | * Specifies whether the button in a "disabled" state |
| `isLoading` | `boolean` | No | * Specifies if the button is isLoading state. Loads a spinner |
| `loadingComponent` | `JSX.Element` | No | - |
| `invertedBackgroundColor` | `boolean` | No | - |
| `secondaryLabel` | `string` | No | Second line of text for the button. |

<details>
<summary>Full TypeScript Interface</summary>

```typescript
export interface ButtonProps
  extends Omit<ThemeableElement<'button'>, 'children'> {
  /** Used to define the label read out by screen-reader when there is no visual label or label is not descriptive enough  */
  'aria-label'?: string;
  /** This prop is used for testing purposes */
  automationId?: string;
  /**
   * Button size - one of small, medium, large
   *
   * @default medium
   */
  size?: Size;
  /**
   * The semantic flavor of the button.
   * Button purpose - one of standard, passive, special, destructive, or complementary
   *
   * @default standard
   */
  purpose?: Purpose;
  /**
   * How the background prioritizes the button.
   * Button priority - one of primary, secondary or tertiary
   * Not related to SVG priority.
   *
   * @default primary
   */
  priority?: Priority;
  /**
   * true: Always take the width of your container
   * false: Width is based on content size
   * responsive: Full Width on mobile - fit-to-content on stationary
   */
  fullWidth?: boolean | 'responsive';

  /**
   * Specifies whether the button in a "disabled" state
   */
  disabled?: boolean;

  /**
   * Specifies if the button is isLoading state. Loads a spinner
   */
  isLoading?: boolean;

  /**
   * Specify the component to render when isLoading === true
   * When not specified, will render children no matter the value of isLoading
   */
  loadingComponent?: JSX.Element;

  /**
   * Specify what the background color is of the container component the button is rendered in to
   * make sure the button is still rendered appropriately. This is used to enable theming such as
   * "light mode buttons on dark backgrounds", which have a different spec than just a "dark mode" button
   */
  invertedBackgroundColor?: boolean;

  /** Second line of text for the button. */
  secondaryLabel?: string;
}

export type Size = 'small' | 'medium' | 'large';

export type Purpose = 'standard' | 'passive' | 'special' | 'destructive' | 'complementary' | 'ai';

export type Priority = 'primary' | 'secondary' | 'tertiary';
```

</details>

## Design Variants

The following variant axes control the component's visual appearance:

### Purpose → use prop `purpose`

- `Standard` **(default)**
- `Passive`
- `Destructive`
- `Special Use`
- `Complementary (Dark Backgrounds)`
- `AI`

### Priority → use prop `priority`

- `Primary` **(default)**
- `Secondary`
- `Tertiary`

### State

- `Default` **(default)**
- `Hover`
- `Active`
- `Focus`
- `Disabled`
- `Processing`

### Size → use prop `size`

- `Small`
- `Medium` **(default)**
- `Large`

### Additional Design Controls

| Control | Type | Default | Description |
| --- | --- | --- | --- |
| Left Icon | boolean | false | - |
| Right Icon | boolean | false | - |
| Label | text | Label | Second line of text for the button. |
| ↳ Secondary Label | text | Secondary label | Second line of text for the button. |
| Secondary Label | boolean | false | Second line of text for the button. |
| ↳ Right Icon | instance_swap | 131828:5971 | - |
| ↳ Left Icon | instance_swap | 131828:5971 | - |

